An appeal was presumably made to the king by Gryme’s party, as in December, 1460 (111116 111016 111311 two months after the riot), a patent was issued condemning the action of the rioters, and commanding that the election should take place according to the ancient custom¹; but despite this, Bagworth retained the mayoralty.
